df-smat
blocks.content: Define a function generating submatrices of an integer-indexed matrix. The function maps an index in ` ( ( 1 ... M ) X. ( 1 ... N ) ) ` into a new index in ` ( ( 1 ... ( M - 1 ) ) X. ( 1 ... ( N - 1 ) ) ) ` . A submatrix is obtained by deleting a row and a column of the original matrix. Because this function re-indexes the matrix, the resulting submatrix still has the same index set for rows and columns, and its determinent is defined, unlike the current ~ df-subma . (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 18-Aug-2020.)
blocks.origin:
axiom df-smat(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4) {
  |- wceq(csmat, cmpt(s0, universe, cmpo(s1, s2, cn, cn, ccom(cv(s0), cmpo(s3, s4, cn, cn, cop(cif(cv(s3), co(cv(s3), caddc, nat1), wbr(cv(s3), clt, cv(s1))), cif(cv(s4), co(cv(s4), caddc, nat1), wbr(cv(s4), clt, cv(s2)))))))))
  -| diffss(s3, s4)
  -| diffss(s1, s3)
  -| diffss(s2, s3)
  -| diffss(s0, s3)
  -| diffss(s1, s4)
  -| diffss(s2, s4)
  -| diffss(s0, s4)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
}

axiom df-smat(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4) {

  ‚ä£ d(s3, s4)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, s3)
  ‚ä£ d(s2, s3)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s3)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, s4)
  ‚ä£ d(s2, s4)

  ‚ä¢ ((c0 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c2 ‚àà c3)‚Üí(c0[(subMat1 ` c2)]c1)=(c2 ‚àò(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]c0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]c1, s1,(s1[+]1))>)))
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s1)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c1)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, c1)
} = {
  ovmpt2d(hs0, hs1, c0, (subMat1 ` c2), c1, (c2 ‚àò(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]c0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]c1, s1,(s1[+]1))>)), cn, cn, (c2 ‚àò(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]hs0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1))>)), universe, (c0 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c2 ‚àà c3))
  syl((c0 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c2 ‚àà c3), (subMat1 ` c2)=(hs0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, hs1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶(c2 ‚àò(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]hs0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1))>))), c2 ‚àà ùïå)
  3ad2ant3(c0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, c1 ‚àà ‚Ñï, c2 ‚àà c3, c2 ‚àà ùïå)
  elex(c2, c3)

  coeq1(hs2, c2, (s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]hs0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1))>))
  df-smat(hs2, hs0, hs1, s0, s1)
  mpt2ex(hs0, hs1, cn, cn, (c2 ‚àò(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]hs0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1))>)))
  coeq2d(c2, (s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]hs0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1))>), (s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]c0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]c1, s1,(s1[+]1))>), ((c0 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c2 ‚àà c3)‚àß(hs0 = c0 ‚àß hs1 = c1)))
  adantl((c0 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚àß c2 ‚àà c3), (hs0 = c0 ‚àß hs1 = c1), (s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]hs0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1))>)=(s0 ‚àà ‚Ñï, s1 ‚àà ‚Ñï ‚Ü¶ < if(s0[<]c0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]c1, s1,(s1[+]1))>))

  ifbid(s0, (s0[+]1), hs0 = c0, s0[<]hs0, s0[<]c0)
  breq2(hs0, c0, s0, clt)

  opeq2d(if(s0[<]c0, s0,(s0[+]1)), if(s1[<]hs1, s1,(s1[+]1)), if(s1[<]c1, s1,(s1[+]1)), hs1 = c1)
  ifbid(s1, (s1[+]1), hs1 = c1, s1[<]hs1, s1[<]c1)
  breq2(hs1, c1, s1, clt)

blocks.name: submatminr1
blocks.content: If we take a submatrix by removing the row ` I ` and column ` J ` , then the result is the same on the matrix with row ` I ` and column ` J ` modified by the ` minMatR1 ` operator. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 25-Aug-2020.)
